headline: Shares of Trade-Vulnerable Retailers Tumble
summary: Stocks of U.S. retailers dependent on international trade fell Monday morning. The moves come after Trump announced over the weekend he would increase the global tariff rate to 15%, up from the 10% he announced on Friday.

headline: 1 S&P 500 Stock for Long-Term Investors and 2 We Turn Down
summary: The S&P 500 (^GSPC) is often seen as a benchmark for strong businesses, but that doesn’t mean every stock is worth owning. Some companies face significant challenges, whether it’s stagnating growth, heavy debt, or disruptive new competitors.
